3 (a) (1) The Department is the principal unit of State government responsible
4 for developing, maintaining, revising, and enforcing statewide disability policies and
5 standards throughout the units of State government.
6 (2) In this capacity, the Department shall:
7 (i) serve as the principal advisor to the Governor on the means and
8 methods available to:
9 1. implement and fund support to individuals with
10 disabilities in accordance with the State Disabilities Plan;
11 2. modify or consolidate support to individuals with
12 disabilities; and
13 3. collaborate with federal, regional, and local units of
14 government to enhance the effectiveness of the provision and funding of support to
15 individuals with disabilities;
16 (ii) annually recommend projects to the Department of Budget and
17 Management for inclusion in the capital budget to promote access to State–owned facilities
18 for individuals with disabilities;
19 (iii) assist units of State government to identify federal, State, local,
20 and private funds available to the State for programs and services for individuals with
21 disabilities; and
22 (iv) provide technical assistance to local jurisdictions in planning and
23 implementing collaborative strategies consistent with the State Disabilities Plan.
24 (b) The Department shall oversee and administer the following programs and
25 units:
26 (1) constituent services and ombudsmen programs;
27 (2) the Assistive Technology Guaranteed Loan Program under Subtitle 6
28 of this title;
29 (3) the Office of Personal Assistance Services, including the Attendant
30 Care Program under Subtitle 4 of this title;
31 (4) Telecommunications Access of Maryland under Subtitle 8 of this title;
