5 SUBTITLE 12. MARYLAND DISABILITY SERVICE ANIMAL PROGRAM.
6 7–1201.
7 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
8 INDICATED.
9 (B) “DEPARTMENT” MEANS THE DEPARTMENT OF DISABILITIES.
10 (C) “ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUAL” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL WITH A DISABILITY, AS
11 DEFINED IN THE FEDERAL AMERICANS WITH DISABILITIES ACT OF 1990, 42 U.S.C.
12 § 12102.
13 (D) “FUND” MEANS THE MARYLAND DISABILITY SERVICE ANIMAL
14 PROGRAM FUND.
15 (E) “NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITY” MEANS A CORPORATION, A
16 FOUNDATION, OR ANY OTHER LEGAL ENTITY THAT:
17 (1) IS TAX–EXEMPT UNDER § 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE
18 CODE;
19 (2) ENGAGES IN THE TRAINING OF SERVICE ANIMALS FOR USE BY
20 ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS; AND
21 (3) HAS BEEN SELECTED BY THE DEPARTMENT TO PROVIDE
22 SERVICES UNDER THIS SUBTITLE.
23 (F) “PROGRAM” MEANS THE MARYLAND DISABILITY SERVICE ANIMAL
24 PROGRAM ESTABLISHED UNDER THIS SUBTITLE.
25 (G) “PROGRAM PARTICIPANT” MEANS AN ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUAL WHO
26 PARTICIPATES IN THE PROGRAM.
27 (H) (1) “SERVICE ANIMAL” MEANS AN ANIMAL THAT IS INDIVIDUALLY
28 TRAINED TO DO WORK OR PERFORM TASKS FOR THE BENEFIT OF AN INDIVIDUAL
29 WITH A DISABILITY.

4 SENATE BILL 157
1 (2) “SERVICE ANIMAL” DOES NOT INCLUDE AN ANIMAL THAT:
2 (I) AS A RESULT OF THE ANIMAL’S PRESENCE, IS MEANT TO
3 DETER CRIME; OR
4 (II) PROVIDES ONLY EMOTIONAL SUPPORT, WELL–BEING,
5 COMFORT, OR COMPANIONSHIP TO AN INDIVIDUAL.
6 (I) “SUCCESSFUL PROGRAM PARTICIPANT” MEANS A PROGRAM
7 PARTICIPANT WHO SUCCESSFULLY COMPLETES THE TRAINING PROTOCOL
8 SPECIFIED BY A NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITY.
9 7–1202.
10 THERE IS A MARYLAND DISABILITY SERVICE ANIMAL PROGRAM IN THE
11 DEPARTMENT.
12 7–1203.
13 THE PURPOSES OF THE PROGRAM ARE TO:
14 (1) REFER ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS WHO INQUIRE ABOUT
15 PARTICIPATION IN THE PROGRAM TO ONE OR MORE NONPROFIT TRAINING
16 ENTITIES;
17 (2) PROVIDE ADDITIONAL FUNDING MECHANISMS TO ASSIST
18 ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS IN THE PROGRAM; AND
19 (3) ENCOURAGE SUCCESSFUL PROGRAM PARTICIPANTS TO ASSIST IN
20 OUTREACH AND REFERRALS TO OTHER ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS WHO COULD
21 BENEFIT FROM PARTICIPATION IN THE PROGRAM.
22 7–1204.
23 THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:
24 (1) MANAGE, SUPERVISE, AND ADMINISTER THE PROGRAM;
25 (2) ADOPT REGULATIONS TO IMPLEMENT THE PROGRAM AND TO
26 ENSURE THAT FUND RESOURCES ARE UTILIZED TO CARRY OUT THE PURPOSES OF
27 THE PROGRAM, INCLUDING REGULATIONS ESTABLISHING PROCEDURES FOR THE
28 DEPARTMENT TO:

SENATE BILL 157 5
1 (I) PROMOTE THE PROGRAM TO ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS
2 THROUGH THE DEPARTMENT’S OUTREACH METHODS;
3 (II) REFER ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS TO SELECTED NONPROFIT
4 TRAINING ENTITIES;
5 (III) RECEIVE DONATIONS FOR THE FUND; AND
6 (IV) USE REVENUE FROM THE FUND TO PAY SELECTED
7 NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITIES FOR SERVICES THAT ARE PROVIDED THROUGH THE
8 PROGRAM; AND
9 (3) SELECT AT LEAST ONE NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITY TO:
10 (I) DEVELOP AND IMPLEMENT A TRAINING PROTOCOL THAT
11 WILL TEACH EACH PROGRAM PARTICIPANT METHODOLOGIES, STRATEGIES, AND
12 TECHNIQUES FOR PARTNERING WITH SERVICE ANIMALS;
13 (II) SELECT QUALIFIED PROGRAM PARTICIPANTS FROM THOSE
14 ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS REFERRED TO THE NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITY UNDER
15 THE PROGRAM;
16 (III) SELECT AN APPROPRIATE SERVICE ANIMAL FOR EACH
17 PROGRAM PARTICIPANT;
18 (IV) FACILITATE EACH PROGRAM PARTICIPANT’S TRAINING
19 USING THE NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITY’S TRAINING PROTOCOL; AND
20 (V) PARTNER EACH SUCCESSFUL PROGRAM PARTICIPANT WITH
21 THE SERVICE ANIMAL ON THE PROGRAM PARTICIPANT’S SUCCESSFUL COMPLETION
22 OF THE NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITY’S TRAINING PROTOCOL.
23 7–1205.
24 (A) TO BE ELIGIBLE FOR SELECTION AS A NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITY
25 UNDER § 7–1204 OF THIS SUBTITLE, A NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITY SHALL:
26 (1) SERVE THE NEEDS OF ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS IN THE STATE; AND
27 (2) GENERATE ITS OWN REVENUE AND REINVEST THE PROCEEDS OF
28 THAT REVENUE IN THE GROWTH AND DEVELOPMENT OF ITS PROGRAMS.
29 (B) A NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITY MAY DISQUALIFY A PROGRAM
30 PARTICIPANT FROM PARTICIPATION IN THE PROGRAM IF THE NONPROFIT

6 SENATE BILL 157
1 TRAINING ENTITY DETERMINES THAT THE PROGRAM PARTICIPANT’S INVOLVEMENT
2 IN THE PROGRAM:
3 (1) PRESENTS A DANGER TO THE PROGRAM PARTICIPANT’S MENTAL
4 OR PHYSICAL WELL–BEING;
5 (2) PRESENTS A DIRECT THREAT TO OTHERS, AS DEFINED BY THE
6 FEDERAL AMERICANS WITH DISABILITIES ACT;
7 (3) PRESENTS A DIRECT THREAT TO THE SERVICE ANIMAL’S MENTAL
8 OR PHYSICAL WELL–BEING; OR
9 (4) DOES NOT MEET THE TRAINING REQUIREMENTS OF THE
10 NONPROFIT.
11 (C) A PROGRAM PARTICIPANT MAY DISCONTINUE INVOLVEMENT IN THE
12 PROGRAM FOR ANY REASON.
13 7–1206.
14 (A) THERE IS A MARYLAND DISABILITY SERVICE ANIMAL PROGRAM FUND.
15 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO:
16 (1) PAY A NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITY; AND
17 (2) COVER THE COSTS OF ADMINISTERING THE PROGRAM.
18 (C) THE SECRETARY SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUND.
19 (D) (1) THE FUND IS A SPECIAL, NONLAPSING FUND THAT IS NOT
20 SUBJECT TO § 7–302 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
21 (2) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL HOLD THE FUND, AND THE
22 COMPTROLLER SHALL ACCOUNT FOR THE FUND.
23 (E) (1) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:
24 (I) REVENUE COLLECTED BY THE DEPARTMENT IN THE FORM
25 OF DONATIONS TO THE PROGRAM;
26 (II) MONEY APPROPRIATED IN THE STATE BUDGET TO THE
27 FUND; AND

SENATE BILL 157 7
1 (III) ANY OTHER MONEY FROM ANY OTHER SOURCE ACCEPTED
2 FOR THE BENEFIT OF THE FUND.
3 (2) EXPENDITURES FROM THE FUND MAY BE MADE ONLY IN
4 ACCORDANCE WITH THE STATE BUDGET.
5 (3) MONEY EXPENDED FROM THE FUND IS SUPPLEMENTAL TO AND IS
6 NOT INTENDED TO TAKE THE PLACE OF FUNDING THAT OTHERWISE WOULD BE
7 APPROPRIATED FOR THE PROGRAM.
8 (F) THE FUND MAY BE USED ONLY TO PAY:
9 (1) A NONPROFIT TRAINING ENTITY; AND
10 (2) ADMINISTRATIVE COSTS OF THE PROGRAM.
11 (G) (1) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL INVEST AND REINVEST THE
12 MONEY OF THE FUND IN THE SAME MANNER AS OTHER STATE MONEY MAY BE
13 INVESTED.
14 (2) ANY INVESTMENT EARNINGS OF THE FUND SHALL BE CREDITED
15 TO THE GENERAL FUND OF THE STATE.
16 (H) FOR THE PURPOSE OF IMPLEMENTING THIS SECTION, THE
17 DEPARTMENT MAY ACCEPT GIFTS OR GRANTS FOR DONATION TO THE FUND.
18 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
19 October 1, 2025.
